result.execSummary:
The defendant Nicole A Josephson was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Misappropriate ID Info - Obtain Money, a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.201(2)(a).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Nicole A Josephson in court, in custody, with Attorney Chelsea Williamson for Attorney Ronald James Sonderhouse.   Ted S. Szczupakiewicz appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant enters a guilty plea to Count #1.  Court performs plea colloquy and finds Defendant guilty of Count #1.  Count #2 is dismissed and read-in.  State makes sentencing recommendations.  Attorney Williamson makes statements regarding sentencing.  Defendant makes statements.  Court sentences the Defendant to the following:

COUNT #1:  IMPOSED AND STATYED SENTENCE OF:    

4 YEARS  IMPRISONMENT (CREDIT - days (to be determined- Attorney Williamson to inform the court within 10 days) )    **CONSECUTIVE TO PRESENT SENTENCES**
  -  2 YEARS  OF INITIAL CONFINEMENT
  -  2 YEARS  OF EXTENDED SUPERVISON 

TERM OF PROBATION:  3 YEARS - Consecutive to Present Sentences per Judge Bohren

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION/EXTENDED SUPERVISON:  
____AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
____Absolute Sobriety;  Random U.A.'s ; 
____No Use or Possession of alcohol or illegal drugs 
____No Use or Possession of prescription drugs without a valid prescription;
____Maintain employment and/or combination of schooling 
____12 step program and attend 2 self-help meetings per week
____Obtain sponsor within 60 days of release
____DNA sample to be provided if not yet previously done
____10 Hours of Community Service for each year of probation (3 years)
____Mental Heath / Psychological Evaluation and treatment deemed appropriate


COSTS:  $278.00 & $250.00 DNA surcharge (to be paid at $50.00 per month, commencing 3 months after release, alternate 11 days jail if not paid) as a condition of probation.
